      "comment": "TUMBY BAY (4) has missed the frame the last couple but was a Grade 4 winner three back (20.59) at this track over 365m. Has the ability and expected to go close. GOODBYE MATE (1) pinged the lids from out wide but run ended and faded out of it late when 8th at Richmond in Grade 5 company. The form out of his last race has been franked. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. GEOSTORM (8) was a course and distance winner (20.79) last time also from the same draw, scoring by 1.5 lengths in a Grade 5. Rates a leading chance again. WHITE AND BLACK (2) has claims again if she runs up to the latest effort.",
